Let R be a Ring. Let M and N be R-modules. We define the Product Module M\oplus  N to consist of the Abelian group M\times  N equipped with scalar multiplication
\begin {split}&R\times  (M\oplus  N)\to  M\oplus  N\\ &(r,(m,n))\mapsto  r\cdot (m,n)=(rm,rn)\end {split}
Note: this is also called the External Direct Sum of M and N.

